name: David Harris
text:
A fine friendly group of people  own & operate this  fishing spot.   There are many varieties of fish to be caught here  .
There's free parking full access by wheelchair.   Public restrooms 🚻.
Disabled people normally get treated pretty good  by staff.
There is a bait & tackle shop . With snacks  😋  .
Yes  , there is also beer.
Rental fishing equipment is available  .
Saltwater license is not mandatory here.  But it doesn't hurt to have it anyway  .
Come , watch the sun 🌞 rises and watch the sun 🌞  sets  . Mostly , just Enjoy your time and relax.

name: Rajesh Shah
text: The sunset here is beautiful. Must wait if you visiting Dauphin Island in evening.

name: Mary Ann Fournier
text: Dauphin Island has so many things to offer anyone looking for a great getaway. We drove from one end to the other, absolutely beautiful place to relax and enjoy timeless beauty!

text: The pier has been damaged, but in keeping the spirit of fishing alive, the locals still flock to what's left of the planks held together by hope alone. It is a great place to fish and you're guaranteed to hear a story or 2 if ya drop in.
